                        <additions>
                            <list>
                                <item xml:id="a1">
                                    <locus from="1r" to="2r"/>
                                    <desc type="Excerpt">Geographical Treatise from the <title type="incomplete" ref="LIT6936TarWaAmidBeta"/> in a very crude hand on two guard leaves. 
                                        Some words or single letter on <locus target="#1r"/> are erased due to the contact 
                                        with the wooden book cover. The short fragment was used in the following editions:
                                        <bibl><ptr target="bm:Krackovskij1912Geography"/></bibl>,
                                        <bibl><ptr target="bm:KrackovskijFrantsouzoff2015Geography"/></bibl> and
                                        <bibl><ptr target="bm:Hoffmann2021Amid"/></bibl>, where it was given siglum A.</desc>
                                    <q xml:lang="gez">
                                        ኆልቆሙ፡ ለእለ፡ ተጋብኡ። ለሕንፃ፡ ማኅፈድ፡ ፸ወ፪፡ መሳፍንት፡ እምደቂቀ፡ <persName ref="PRS8730Sem">ሴም፡
                                        </persName> ፳ወ፭ብእሲ፡ ወእሉ፡ ኀደሩ፡ እም<placeName ref="LOC3013Euphra">አፍራጥስ፡ </placeName>ወእስከ፡
                                        <placeName ref="LOC5833Syria">ሶርያ፡ </placeName>ወእስከ፡ ጽንፈ፡ ምሥራቅ፡ ወእምኔሆሙ፡ ሶርያውያን፡
                                        ወአእፃዳተ፡ ዘረቢዐ፡ ወደሴተ፡ ወሐራምቃ፡ ከለዳውያን፡ ወእሙንቱ፡ ሰብአ፡ <placeName ref="LOC1692Babylo">ባቢሎን፡
                                        </placeName>ወ<placeName ref="LOC3930Iran">ፋርስ፡ </placeName> ወኵራስን፡
                                        ወፌርያ፡ ወስንድ፡
                                        ወህንዳኬ፡ ወ<placeName ref="LOC6387Yemen">የማን</placeName>፡
                                        ወጣይፍ፡ ወተማማ፡ ወ፪አብሕርት፡ ወዘመደ፡ <placeName ref="ETH1134Arab">ዐረብ፡</placeName> ወእለ፡ የአምሩ፡ ጽሒፈ፡ ሆኅያት፡ ፰<placeName ref="ETH1678Hebrew">እብራዊ፡
                                        </placeName>ወሥየናዊ፡ ወፋርሳዊ፡  ወካልዳዊ፡ ወሲኒ፡
                                        ወኃማዚ፡ ወ<placeName ref="ETH1134Arab">ዐረቢ፡ </placeName>
                                        ወሎሙ፡ እምአብሕርት፡ <placeName ref="LOC3013Euphra">ኤፍራጦስ</placeName>፡ ወፈለገ፡ በለከ፡</q>
                                    <q type="translation" xml:lang="de">
                                        <ab>The number of people gathered for the construction of the tower was 72 captains. Among them were of Shem's 
                                            descendants, 25 men. They lived from the Euphrates to Syria and to the eastern edge. They included the Syrians, the areas
                                            of Rabiʿā (= Diyar Rabi'a), the island of Wäḥarāmqā (= Ǧarāmiqa), the Chaldeans - that is the people of Babylon - as well
                                            as Persia, Khorasan, Fergana, Sind, India, Temān (= Yemen), Ṭayf, Tamāmā (= al-Yamāma) and two seas and the Arabs.
                                            Those who know how to write letters are 8: Hebrew, Syrian, Persian, Indian, Chaldean, Chinese, ḥāmāzi (= Himyaric)
                                            and Arabic. They have the Euphrates and the river Balch as rivers.</ab>
                                    </q>
